    <div class="main review-item" id="6850768">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/6850768/" class="title-link">现象学意义上对死之现象的考察</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-6850768"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/49246213/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/u49246213-7.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/49246213/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">吃糖的亚伯神父</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2014-08-27"
      class="main-meta">2014-08-27 11:45:56</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_6850768_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  与胡塞尔不同，后期胡塞尔对死亡有过现象学考察，但是是将其作为主体性权能的一种界限，特别是在考察身体与先验主体性之间的关系。死亡很大程度上意味着主体的去世界化。  而舍勒则不同，他将死亡视为可当下直观的现象。死亡的被给予性是作为生命的先天本质结构，事实性经验。...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/6850768/#comments">(5回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">2有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_6850768_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_6850768_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
